Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at an event where she praised President Joe Biden's leadership and highlighted the progress the administration has made in various areas. She mentioned the successful handling of the pandemic, the reopening of schools and businesses, and the ongoing infrastructure projects. Harris also emphasized the importance of addressing the climate crisis and commended the efforts of advocates, leaders, and President Biden in leading on climate action. She concluded by introducing Lovette Jacobs, a union worker and electrical apprentice, who spoke next.